{
  "uid": "nexus-worker",
  "title": "Worker \u2014 Queue & Job Execution",
  "tags": [
    "nexus-scheduler",
    "app",
    "worker"
  ],
  "timezone": "browser",
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "version": 1,
  "refresh": "30s",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-6h",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "description": "The BullMQ worker: queue depth, run outcomes, the LibreChat calls that dominate job time, and \u2014 since #104 \u2014 how long runs wait versus work, whether the scheduler is keeping up, and whether the concurrency ceiling is being hit. Runtime names verified against prom-client 15.1.3.",
  "panels": [
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Queue (BullMQ)",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Queue depth by state",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 1
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum by (state) (nexus_scheduler_queue_depth)",
          "legendFormat": "{{state}}"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Rising `waiting` with flat `active` means the worker is saturated or wedged. Sustained `delayed` growth points at retries/backoff. This gauge is pull-based with a 2s timeout guard, so gaps here mean Redis was slow to answer, not that the queue was empty."
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Backlog growth",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 1
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "deriv(sum(nexus_scheduler_queue_depth{state=\"waiting\"})[10m:])",
          "legendFormat": "waiting +/- per sec"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The derivative is the leading indicator: a persistently positive slope means arrival outpaces completion and the backlog will not drain on its own."
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Run outcomes",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 9
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Runs by status",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 10
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "ops"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum by (status) (rate(nexus_scheduler_runs_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{status}}"
        }
      ],
      "description": "nexus_scheduler_runs_total. Gaps to be aware of (#104): CANCELLED is never recorded, and a timeout is indistinguishable from a generic failure."
    },
    {
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Success rate",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 10
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percentunit",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "orange",
                "value": 0.9
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 0.98
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum(rate(nexus_scheduler_runs_total{status=\"success\"}[30m])) / clamp_min(sum(rate(nexus_scheduler_runs_total[30m])), 0.0001)",
          "legendFormat": "success"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Runs (24h)",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 18,
        "y": 10
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum(increase(nexus_scheduler_runs_total[24h]))",
          "legendFormat": "runs"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Volume for the day \u2014 context for every rate above."
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "LibreChat calls \u2014 where job time goes",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 17
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Call latency vs job timeout",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 16,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 18
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "orange",
                "value": 300
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 600
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(nexus_scheduler_librechat_call_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p50"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(nexus_scheduler_librechat_call_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95"
        },
        {
          "refId": "C",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(nexus_scheduler_librechat_call_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p99"
        }
      ],
      "description": "p95 approaching DEFAULT_JOB_TIMEOUT_SECONDS (600s, red) is the early warning that runs are about to be killed. The histogram's largest bucket is 300s, so anything slower is unresolvable \u2014 it lands in +Inf and the quantile flattens (#104)."
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Calls / sec",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 18
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "reqps"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum(rate(nexus_scheduler_librechat_call_duration_seconds_count[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "calls/s"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Derived from the histogram's _count \u2014 the only throughput signal available for model calls today."
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Node.js runtime \u2014 saturation signals",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 26
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Event loop lag (p99 / mean)",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 27
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "nodejs_eventloop_lag_p99_seconds{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "p99"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "nodejs_eventloop_lag_mean_seconds{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "mean"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The single best saturation signal for a Node process: when the loop lags, everything queues behind it \u2014 requests, timers and job callbacks alike."
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Heap used vs total",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 8,
        "y": 27
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "bytes"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "nodejs_heap_size_used_bytes{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "used"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "nodejs_heap_size_total_bytes{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "total"
        },
        {
          "refId": "C",
          "expr": "process_resident_memory_bytes{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "rss"
        }
      ],
      "description": "RSS climbing while heap stays flat points outside the JS heap \u2014 native buffers, or Chromium in the PDF path."
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "GC time",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 27
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percentunit"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum by (kind) (rate(nodejs_gc_duration_seconds_sum{service=\"worker\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{kind}}"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Fraction of wall-clock spent in GC, by collection kind. A rising `major` share means the heap is under real pressure, not just busy."
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "CPU",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 34
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percentunit"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "rate(process_cpu_seconds_total{service=\"worker\"}[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "cores"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Node is single-threaded: sustained values near 1 core mean this process is the bottleneck."
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Active handles",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 8,
        "y": 34
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "nodejs_active_handles_total{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "handles"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Steadily climbing handles with flat throughput is the classic leak signature (sockets or timers never released)."
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Open file descriptors",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 34
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "process_open_fds{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "open"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "process_max_fds{service=\"worker\"}",
          "legendFormat": "max"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Approaching max_fds means new connections start failing."
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Scheduler \u2014 the heart of the product",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 40
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Scheduler ticks by result",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 41
      },
      "description": "Requires the worker instrumentation from PR #110 (feat/genai-metrics-model-labels) \u2014 tick, schedule-claim, queue-wait, run-duration and throttling metrics are registered there, not on main. Verified live with #110 built in: all these panels populate (scheduled fires claimed, queue-wait p95 51.7s under a run burst). Until #110 merges, empty here means 'not instrumented yet', not a scheduler failure.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum by (result) (rate(nexus_scheduler_tick_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{result}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Tick duration (p95) vs the tick interval",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 41
      },
      "description": "Requires the worker instrumentation from PR #110 (feat/genai-metrics-model-labels) \u2014 tick, schedule-claim, queue-wait, run-duration and throttling metrics are registered there, not on main. Verified live with #110 built in: all these panels populate (scheduled fires claimed, queue-wait p95 51.7s under a run burst). Until #110 merges, empty here means 'not instrumented yet', not a scheduler failure.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(nexus_scheduler_tick_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Schedule fires: claimed vs missed",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 49
      },
      "description": "Requires the worker instrumentation from PR #110 (feat/genai-metrics-model-labels) \u2014 tick, schedule-claim, queue-wait, run-duration and throttling metrics are registered there, not on main. Verified live with #110 built in: all these panels populate (scheduled fires claimed, queue-wait p95 51.7s under a run burst). Until #110 merges, empty here means 'not instrumented yet', not a scheduler failure.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum(rate(nexus_scheduler_schedules_claimed_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "claimed/s"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "sum(rate(nexus_scheduler_schedules_missed_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "MISSED/s"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Capacity \u2014 waiting vs working",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 56
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Queue wait vs run duration (p95)",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 57
      },
      "description": "Requires the worker instrumentation from PR #110 (feat/genai-metrics-model-labels) \u2014 tick, schedule-claim, queue-wait, run-duration and throttling metrics are registered there, not on main. Verified live with #110 built in: all these panels populate (scheduled fires claimed, queue-wait p95 51.7s under a run burst). Until #110 merges, empty here means 'not instrumented yet', not a scheduler failure.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(nexus_scheduler_queue_wait_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "queue wait p95"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(nexus_scheduler_run_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "run duration p95"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Run duration by outcome (p95)",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 57
      },
      "description": "Requires the worker instrumentation from PR #110 (feat/genai-metrics-model-labels) \u2014 tick, schedule-claim, queue-wait, run-duration and throttling metrics are registered there, not on main. Verified live with #110 built in: all these panels populate (scheduled fires claimed, queue-wait p95 51.7s under a run burst). Until #110 merges, empty here means 'not instrumented yet', not a scheduler failure.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le, status) (rate(nexus_scheduler_run_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "{{status}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Throttling against the configured ceiling",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "mimir"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 65
      },
      "description": "Requires the worker instrumentation from PR #110 (feat/genai-metrics-model-labels) \u2014 tick, schedule-claim, queue-wait, run-duration and throttling metrics are registered there, not on main. Verified live with #110 built in: all these panels populate (scheduled fires claimed, queue-wait p95 51.7s under a run burst). Until #110 merges, empty here means 'not instrumented yet', not a scheduler failure.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum by (scope) (rate(nexus_scheduler_runs_throttled_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{scope}} throttled/s"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "nexus_scheduler_concurrency_limit",
          "legendFormat": "{{scope}} limit"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}